Yes, in Material-UI (MUI) DataGrid, you can customize the filter options to include a "not equals" filter.

To achieve this, you'll need to define a custom filter operator for the DataGrid. Here's an example of how to add a "not equals" filter option for your DataGrid:

import { DataGrid, GridToolbar } from '@mui/x-data-grid';
import { useState } from 'react';

const CustomDataGrid = () => {
  const [rows, setRows] = useState([
    { id: 1, server: 'lelvdck.com' },
    { id: 2, server: 'mydck-prod.com' },
    { id: 3, server: 'mydck-dev.com' },
    { id: 4, server: 'another-server.com' }
  ]);

  const columns = [
    { field: 'id', headerName: 'ID', width: 90 },
    { field: 'server', headerName: 'Server', width: 200 }
  ];

  const customFilterOperator = {
    label: 'Not equals',
    value: 'notEquals',
    getApplyFilterFn: (filterItem) => {
      if (!filterItem.value) {
        return null;
      }
      return (params) =>
        params.value !== filterItem.value;
    },
    InputComponent: (props) => (
      <input
        type="text"
        value={props.item.value || ''}
        onChange={(e) => props.applyValue({ ...props.item, value: e.target.value })}
        placeholder="Enter server name"
      />
    ),
  };

  return (
    <div style={{ height: 400, width: '100%' }}>
      <DataGrid
        rows={rows}
        columns={columns}
        filterModel={{
          items: [{ columnField: 'server', operatorValue: 'notEquals', value: 'lelvdck.com' }]
        }}
        components={{ Toolbar: GridToolbar }}
        columnTypes={{
          server: {
            filterOperators: [
              ...DataGrid.defaultProps.columnTypes.server.filterOperators,
              customFilterOperator,
            ],
          },
        }}
      />
    </div>
  );
};

export default CustomDataGrid;

In this example:

We define a custom filter operator named "Not equals" (customFilterOperator).

This operator checks if the value in the column doesn't match the filter input and applies it to the server column.

You can modify the value in filterModel to pre-filter the data or allow users to enter their own input via the toolbar.


This setup allows users to filter rows where the server name is not equal to "lelvdck.com".

